@node "Quick" " MV Mail 1.32 - Quick installation reference !"

To quick put in run your @{b}Mad Virgin BW MAIL DOOR@{ub} just do following:

 - Use suplied Installer Install script for MV Mail door, and allow it
   to make changes in your DayDream.CFG file.

 - Edit @{"MAIL.TAGS" link mail.tags.cfg} file to match your message bases
   or use MAKETAGS utils to create this file, and then copy it from RAM:
   to Doors:MV/MAIL/ directory.

 - If you have FIDONET style networks, you have to edit @{"MAIL.NET" link mail.net.cfg} 
   file to match your message bases

 - Run @{"OperatorConfig" link mail.cfg} (located in DayDream:Utils/ dir)
 
 - Run DayDream
 
 - Enter MAIL at DayDream's prompt

 - Enjoy ! :)

@endnode

@node "Introd" " MVMail 1.32 - Introduction"
@next "disclaim"
@prev "main"

 Idea for this door become from Freak (freak@alife.dv.co.yu) and Teorist 
 (teorist@eros.dv.co.yu).

 Many DayDream Sysops want to make their BBS fully operational as a
 conference oriented Bulletin board system. It was not so easy if You
 used original Grab 2.0 mail door. It has a lot of disadvantages that
 makes it realy unreliable for operating as a good system.

 Mad Virgin Mail offers you a few brand new features, seen in BW doors
 on PC BBS software, and a little more.

 Advantages :

    - You may use three archivers for MAIL Packets (LHA/LZX/ZIP)
    - Pretty good security checks, that disallows users to hack their
      replys, and now there is no chance to fake mails
    - Sysops may configure :
        - Maximal number of messages per message base in one packet
        - Maximal number of messages in one packet
        - Maximal lenght of unpacked .DAT file

      (user may set this values below sysop default, but no more than it!)

    - Door now may report file attached to message when scaning msg.bases
    - A new SM (select message bases) door
    - Dreamtoss toss all netmails into just one conference, and users
      often forgot to move their reply to adecvate conference - 
      now, MVMail fix it automaticaly.
    - Allow Sysop to make some message bases as READ ONLY
    - Allow Sysop to Force some message bases to user
    - Allow Sysop to put Bulletins into a mail packet
    - Allow User to grab Personal mail only (global or per message base)
    - Allow user to use filters for messages (to trash some users)

@endnode

