@node "Require" "MV Mail - Requirements"
@next "install"
@prev "disclaim"
    
                      @{b}Door requirements@{ub}
                      ----------------- 

You need Amiga OS and DayDream v1.30+ (dreamdoor.library v7+)


Memory requirements :

 This type of door is pretty hungry for your free memory, and if you
 are running Amiga with less than 4MB it is highly recomended to NOT TO
 run any other program while you are runnung DayDream, and assign temp
 directory somewhere on your HardDisk drive, not to RAM:

Lets explain....

 This Mail door had possibility to set how many messages user may DL  in one
packet. This options make no possibility to set LRP relaying on Highest
message information, but it have to create a field to 'remember' these
informations. If your BBS have 255 conferences with 64 message bases, door
will allocate 64 * 254 * 2 bytes (if it cannot allocate this memory, it will
quit !) - this means that in normal use door will need about 250KB of free
memory block.

In MVMail v1.24 or higher Sysop may define Copy buffer for attached files. (it
is recomended to use at least 16354 bytes for buffer)
@endnode

@node "Install" " MV Mail - Instalation "
@next "Features"
@prev "Require"


It is highly recomended to use supplied INSTALL script for instaling 
                        MV MAIL Door. 

To use it, simply unpack archive (you have to extract archive with
enabled "Extract files with full path" option!) on any device, and
simply click on INSTALL icon.

MV MAIL uses standard Commodore INSTALLER for instalation procedure.


@endnode

