@node "123b" "MV Mail - Changes in Version 1.23b"

    Changes in version 1.23b:

    - Put Origin line into Echo/Mail messages
    - Fixed some minor bugs.
    - Grab all Private messages into a Sysops packet
    - Set Sysop Default values for a user who start door for a first time
    - Changed UL sequence
    - Changed DL sequence
    - Inform user when setting LRP files
    - Removed AREA: string from Netmails
    - Do not write User.cfg when exiting door
    - New version of SMB (select message base) - v1.4
    - Mail & SMB configs moved into a Doors:mv/mail directory

@endnode

@node "124b" "MV Mail - Changes in Version 1.24b"

    Changes in version 1.24b:

    - Added Read Only flag into a SMB
    - Added MAIL.NET config 
            (for fixing Dreamtoss problem with Netmail conferences)
    - Sysop may set COPY BUFFER size
    - Sysop may disable RESUME MAIL option
    - Sysop may set door to delete saved mail packet after Upload
    - Added flags for auto Upload/Download/Resume (in Externalcommands.dat)

@endnode

@node "125b" "MV Mail - Changes in Version 1.25b"

    Changes in version 1.25b:

    - Door now check READ ONLY flag when user upload packet
    - Door now check conference acces for each uploaded message
    - Optimise LRP during importing new messages (check if the LRP is higher
      than higest message in base)
    - Fixed PKT number increment
    - Fixed counting of Personal messages
    - Check if total number of messages match size of .DAT file
    - Added PERSONAL/ALL switch into a User config
    - Show type of error if occur during upload

@endnode

@node "126b" "MV Mail - Changes in Version 1.26b"

    Changes in version 1.25b:

    - Fixed few problems during UL/DL
    - Fixed error with EALL messages
    - Added support for bulletins
    - Added Logfile option (sysop config)
    - Fixed bug with AREA in Netmail
    - Added Sysop's switch to strip or not control lines (sysop config)
    - Write Operator Config attempt into a Logfile
    

@endnode

@node "127b" "MV Mail - Changes in Version 1.27"

    Changes in version 1.27b:

    - Changed algorhytm for grabbing messages (now door fix some bugs
      into .DAT files that may occure if you use MsgBaseOpt)
    - Sysop may configure to put or not * origin line in Netmail messages

@endnode

@node "128b" "MV Mail - Changes in Version 1.28b"

    Changes in version 1.28b:

    - New version of SMB (v1.5): fixed all(?) bugs, added some user commands,
      look changed for a few details
    - Added timeout for all questions that door make
    - Changed DL/UL look

@endnode

@node "129b" "MV Mail - Changes in Version 1.29b"

    Changes in version 1.29b:


    - New version of SMB (v1.6):
        - User may configure Personal/All downloading for each message base
        - Added new switch 'P' = Personal/All
        - Optimised tag routines

    - Added new controls into a User Config
    - Added FILTER option
@endnode

@node "130b" "MV Mail - Changes in Version 1.30 beta"

    Changes in version 1.30 beta:


 - Log file changed. Much more messages are now written in LOGFILE 
   Logfile is stored in Doors:MV/Mail/Mail_Node(number).LOG
   
 - @{"Operator Config" link mail.cfg} now putted as an external utility with GUI

 - Added 'Can_Forward' and 'Check_mail_destination' flags in @{"Operator Config" link mail.cfg}

 - Fixed trash in Password field in packet

 - Added User CFG switch for users to select weather they DL their own
   messages or not.

 - Set LRP (Last Read Pointers) door now integrated in MV_MAIL

 - MV_Mail outlook totaly changed !
   Sysop now may define almost @{b}ALL@{ub} output from MV_Mail
   Added Display directory in Doors:MV/MAIL/ directory, you have to create
   in it directories as in your DayDream:Display/ directory for GFX/TXT
   files (look carefully at @{"MVM_Display" link MVM_Display}.

 - SysOp now may define ALL allowed nodes for FIONET_MAIL in @{"MAIL.NET" link mail.net.cfg} config.

 - Added mvmail.library for some functions. You @{b}must@{ub} copy it in LIBS:

 - Added @{"MVM-Server" link MVM_Server} to solve all multinode problems.
   it @{b}MUST@{ub} be running to allow you to start MV_Mail.

 - Added 'Abort DL' question before startnig mail packet transfer.

 - Now all menus in MV_Mail get HELP screen.
   To call it, just press H.
   Help screens are stored in #?.help.(GFX|TXT) files in Mail display/mode dir.
              Main Menu   - MAIN_HELP.### (TXT/GFX)
              SMB 1 Menu  - SMB1_HELP.###
              SMB 2 Menu  - SMB2_HELP.###
              USER Menu   - USER_HELP.###
              SetLrp Menu - SETLRP_HELP.###


   If no help file exists, option is automaticaly turned off.

 - Form 1.3 Mv Mail needs DayDream v1.27 or greater to work.


@endnode

@node "130f" "MV Mail - Changes in Version 1.30 final"

    Changes in version 1.30 final:

 - Before starting grab, MVMail now display number of expected messages.

 - User now may abort grab procedure by pressing ESC twice

 - In @{"SMB.CFG" link SMB.CFG} now added third filag to allow user to use
   both realname and alias in same message base

 - SMB again fixed. Seems to be 100% OK now!?

 - In SMB display added MORE to inform user that in this message base
   exsist more bases than displayed.
   In GFX mode door print a '+' mark, and in TXT mode wrote MORE !

 - Fixed a small cursor bug in User Config.

 - Display.dat file changed a little.
   Read 'MV_DISPLAY.DAT' carefully to setup your display correctly.

 - Now user can use Lower&Upper case letters in all MVMAIL menus

@endnode
@node "131" "MV Mail - Changes in Version 1.31"

    Changes in version 1.31:

 - Added 'DUBCheck' option in @{"Operator Config" link mail.cfg}
 - Much more messages are now written in LOGFILE
 - Now MVMail increase UL message counter

@endnode
@node "132" "MV Mail - Changes in Version 1.32"

    Changes in version 1.32:

 - Now for all scaned message bases LRP is set to the last scaned message
 - Fixed some minor bugs.
 - Version is free
 - MVM-Server & mvmail.library aren't needed any more
 - Requires: DD-Server v1.30 & dreamdoor.library v7.0
 
@endnode

